<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10854] record cannot be adjusted by @RecordType annotation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10854</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
@RecordType(defaults=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;, namedVariant=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;)
record Person(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name, Date dob) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//Person(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;,Date)
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//Person(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;)  no!
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//Person(Map)     no!
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//Person()        no!
&lt;/span&gt;
  public Person { &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// implies @TupleConstructor(pre={...})
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; name.length() &amp;gt; 1
  }

  Person(Person that) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;(that.name(), that.dob())
  }

  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//getAt(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i)
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//toList()
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//toMap()
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The goal is to disable all the extra constructors and &lt;tt&gt;@RecordType&lt;/tt&gt; fails to do so.  This is because there is an implicit &lt;tt&gt;@RecordType()&lt;/tt&gt; annotation added by the parser that gets in the way of correct merged attributes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
